  "description" : "[h1]Preface:[/h1]\nThis mod pretty much serves both as integration between the NostOS's intro mission and Project Redemption, making alterations to better fit canon lore, as well as being a Protectorate ship replacer addon to the NostOS. Features include:\n[list]\n[*]The replacement of some loot items in the NostOS intro to bring it in line with the vanilla intro, notably the procedurally generated pistol and the poster have been swapped out for the Damaged Handgun and some salves respectively.\n[*]The introduction of two new items; a new unique weapon and codex, both replacing the procedurally generated dagger and the Terrene Protectorate Field Guide codex respectively within the mission.\n[*]Changes to the dialogue present in the NostOS intro mission and its cinematics for the sake of keeping with canon lore and Project Redemption's additions to it, this has unfortunately meant that the narration in the start of the first cinematic had to be disabled.\n[*]A couple minor object additions to the NostOS intro.\n[*]The NostOS ship has been replaced with Flogeno's Protectorate ship, as it's more unique and makes more sense for the intro. The NostOS ship pet is now also an Orbis instead of a cat.\n[*]As a bonus tweak, NostOS characters craft non-racial armor sets instead of Human ones now, although they no longer have any tier 6 sets as a result (the Perfect set can be used to fill in that gap thankfully).\n[/list]\n\n[h1]Note:[/h1]\nGiven the addition of a \"lost and found\" npc in Project Redemption who sells the Damaged Handgun, and the fact that this mod does disable the voice narration at the very start of the NostOS intro as well as replacing the default NostOS ship, this mod can be considered [b]completely optional[/b]. If you're a person like me who's obsessed with consistency in even the most minor of things, and also are bothered by the lack of their own armor sets and ship pet though, you'll probably want this mod if you're playing the NostOS. There's a chance this mod may not be exactly compatible with [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3571582129]AEONA[/url] either as well.\n\nCredits: Pixelflame for the mod thumbnail, upgraded Neo Tazer sprite and of course the wonderful NostOS mod, Some Some Moe You Don't Know for the Protectorate ship icon sprite, [url=https://steamcommunity.com/id/flogenos]Gunnar (formerly Flogenos)[/url] for the Protectorate ship itself. Chucklefish for base game assets and for this excellent little sandbox game.",
